==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Christian Science
<hw>Christian Science</hw>. <def>A system of healing disease of mind and
body which teaches that all cause and effect is mental, and that sin,
sickness, and death will be destroyed by a full understanding of the
Divine Principle of Jesus' teaching and healing. The system was founded
by Rev. Mary Baker Glover Eddy, of Concord, N. H., in 1866, and bases
its teaching on the Scriptures as understood by its adherents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Christian Scientist</ent>⟦br⟧
